\begin_layout Standard
Once started, the system is fully autonomous and does not access or modify
 any data on the used PC (it only uses the hardware resources such as the
 processor, RAM, screen, mouse, keyboard, etc.), which ensures that:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
there is no dependency between the bootable USB system and the PC being
 used
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Aside from potential hardware incompatibilities
\end_layout

\end_inset

, making it entirely possible to use a personal rather than a professional
 PC for this purpose;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
