\begin_layout Subsection
KeePass
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
KeePass is a password manager that protects sets of passwords (or other
 secrets) within encrypted databases, referred to as "vaults." Accessing
 these vaults requires a master password (the "key"), which must be strong
 to avoid being cracked.
 Each vault corresponds to a file, and there is no server involved.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This software allows you to create one or more vaults for storing your passwords
, whether for personal use or for a team.
 Each vault is protected by its master password.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With KeePass, it’s easy to use strong, unique passwords for each application,
 device, or container.
 It’s also recommended to let KeePass generate these random passwords rather
 than creating them yourself.
\end_layout

